<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-28T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1415: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-28T09:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                        1922—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:50
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>131. Officially informed by the Haitian Government that the Council of
                            State yesterday, October 27th, sanctioned without modification the loan
                            protocol.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
